By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control said the country has recorded 120 fresh cases of #COVID-19 infections. The health agency while announcing this via it’s twitter handle account late Sanday night, said the fresh infections brought total confirmed cases now to 160,657 out of which 145,399 patients have been discharged from across the various isolation facilities in Nigeria. It further stated that fourteen states, including the FCT, reported fresh cases as follows: Lagos-32; Rivers-25; Kaduna-20; Bayelsa-13;Kano-7; Jigawa and Borno-5 each; Abia-4; Oyo-3; Plateau-2 while FCT, Ogun, Nasarawa and Imo State recorded 1 infection each. The NCDC regrettably announced that 2,013 lives has been lost to COVID-19 related ailments since the outbreak of the pandemic in Nigeria. See the schedule for total confirmed cases below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed COVID-19 cases in Nigeria has risen to 54,008 as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Monday recorded 143 fresh infections.Announcing via it's twitter handle, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) said Plateau recorded 35 new cases; Kaduna, 21;… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Lagos State recorded 39 fresh infections and FCT 22 as 100 new cases of COVID-19 were recorded on Sunday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. With the Sunday's figure, the total confirmed cases had risen to 55,005 while total death toll… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Wednesday said it has confirmed 1,138 fresh infections and have so far discharged a total of 108,657 patients since the index case was reported in February 27, 2020 in the country. The new confirmed cases brought… In "Top Stories"